    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Eyewear that protected the eyes from gas and other irritant agents; developed during WWI. Following the introduction of the Small Box Respirator, anti-gas goggles were considered obsolete and their use declined.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
